#: ../../docs/classes/class_tree.rst:325
msgid "enum **SelectMode**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_tree.rst:327
msgid ""
"**SELECT_SINGLE** = **0** --- Allows selection of a single cell at a "
"time. From the perspective of items, only a single item is allowed to be "
"selected. And there is only one column selected in the selected item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_tree.rst:329
msgid ""
"The focus cursor is always hidden in this mode, but it is positioned at "
"the current selection, making the currently selected item the currently "
"focused item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_tree.rst:331
msgid ""
"**SELECT_ROW** = **1** --- Allows selection of a single row at a time. "
"From the perspective of items, only a single items is allowed to be "
"selected. And all the columns are selected in the selected item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_tree.rst:333
msgid ""
"The focus cursor is always hidden in this mode, but it is positioned at "
"the first column of the current selection, making the currently selected "
"item the currently focused item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_tree.rst:335
msgid ""
"**SELECT_MULTI** = **2** --- Allows selection of multiple cells at the "
"same time. From the perspective of items, multiple items are allowed to "
"be selected. And there can be multiple columns selected in each selected "
"item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_tree.rst:337
msgid ""
"The focus cursor is visible in this mode, the item or column under the "
"cursor is not necessarily selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_tree.rst:349
msgid "enum **DropModeFlags**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_tree.rst:351
msgid ""
"**DROP_MODE_DISABLED** = **0** --- Disables all drop sections, but still "
"allows to detect the \"on item\" drop section by "
":ref:`get_drop_section_at_position "
"<class_Tree_method_get_drop_section_at_position>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_tree.rst:353
msgid ""
"**Note:** This is the default flag, it has no effect when combined with "
"other flags."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_tree.rst:355
msgid ""
"**DROP_MODE_ON_ITEM** = **1** --- Enables the \"on item\" drop section. "
"This drop section covers the entire item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_tree.rst:357
msgid ""
"When combined with :ref:`DROP_MODE_INBETWEEN "
"<class_Tree_constant_DROP_MODE_INBETWEEN>`, this drop section halves the "
"height and stays centered vertically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_tree.rst:359
msgid ""
"**DROP_MODE_INBETWEEN** = **2** --- Enables \"above item\" and \"below "
"item\" drop sections. The \"above item\" drop section covers the top half"
" of the item, and the \"below item\" drop section covers the bottom half."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_tree.rst:361
msgid ""
"When combined with :ref:`DROP_MODE_ON_ITEM "
"<class_Tree_constant_DROP_MODE_ON_ITEM>`, these drop sections halves the "
"height and stays on top / bottom accordingly."
msgstr ""

